        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(reply): suppress post-tool-send meta commentary as duplicate reply",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nAfter an agent calls the `message` tool to deliver its main reply in a turn, models sometimes append a trailing acknowledgement (\"已发 #22141\", \"Sent above\", \"核心回答如下\", \"OK\", \"Roger\", \"Got it\"). These acks carry no information beyond the message-tool send itself but reach the channel as a second visible message — a well-known duplicate-reply pattern.\n\nThis was reported upstream as the **F30 / F31 duplicate-reply failure mode**:\n\n> After `message(action=send, ...)` delivers the main reply, the agent's\n> final text often contains a trailing meta-comment (\"主回复已发 (#xxx)\",\n> \"已发\", \"已发 #22141\", \"已发, 不再追加总结\", \"核心回答如下\", \"OK\",\n> \"Sent above\"). This final text gets dispatched as a *second* visible\n> message in the channel.\n\nThe existing `filterMessagingToolDuplicates` only catches full-content duplicates via substring match with a 10-char minimum, so short meta-acks escape it. The issue reproduces reliably across providers and channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.).\n\n## Fix\n\nThis patch adds a complementary filter — `filterMessagingToolMetaCommentary` — that recognises post-tool-send meta commentary by pattern (Chinese + English) and suppresses it from the final reply payload. Wired into both `agent-runner-payloads.ts` and `followup-delivery.ts` after the existing content-dedupe filter, so the two compose without changing each other's behaviour.\n\nThe new filter is intentionally conservative:\n\n- **Only fires when a message-tool send has already happened this turn** (`sentTexts.length > 0`). Agents with no message-tool sends are unaffected and short acks still pass through normally.\n- **Length-capped at 200 chars** and only matches anchored ack patterns.\n- **Substantial trailing content after the ack (> 20 chars) is treated as a real reply** — e.g. \"已发. Now let me explain the architecture ...\" is NOT suppressed.\n- **Media payloads are always preserved**, even if the caption is meta-ack.\n\n### Patterns matched\n\n| Group | Examples |\n| --- | --- |\n| Chinese standalone acks | `已发`, `已发送`, `主回复已发`, `好了`, `收到`, `完毕`, `完成` |\n| Chinese mid-text acks | `核心回答如下`, `总结如下`, `不再追加总结`, `答案如下` |\n| English standalone acks | `OK`, `Okay`, `Sent`, `Done`, `Roger`, `Got it`, `Copy that`, `Acknowledged`, `Posted`, `Replied`, `Done.` |\n| English mid-text | `Replying above`, `Answer below`, `Response above` |\n\nPlus compound forms with a brief trailing comment (≤ 20 chars after the matched phrase), e.g. `OK, that's the fix.`, `已发, 不再追加.`, `已发 #22141.`\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/messaging-dedupe.ts` — new `isPostToolSendMetaCommentary(text)` function and pattern table.\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.ts` — re-export new function.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/reply-payloads-dedupe.ts` — new `filterMessagingToolMetaCommentary({ payloads, sentTexts })`.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/reply-payloads-dedupe.runtime.ts` and `reply-payloads.ts` — barrel re-exports.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-payloads.ts` and `followup-delivery.ts` — wire the new filter after the existing content dedupe.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/reply-payloads.test.ts` — 52 unit tests covering true / false cases, compound acks, length cutoffs, and media-payload preservation.\n\n## Test coverage\n\n| True cases (should suppress) | False cases (must keep) |\n| --- | --- |\n| 已发 / 已发 #22141 / 已发送 / 主回复已发 / 主回复已发 (#22142) | Real replies starting with \"已发\" but continuing with substantive prose |\n| 核心回答如下 / 总结如下 / 不再追加总结 | \"Here is my analysis of the situation.\" |\n| Sent / Sent above / Sent #22141 / Done. / Replied above / Posted. / Acknowledged. | \"Let me check that for you — one moment.\" |\n| OK / Okay / Roger / Got it / Copy that | \"The price is \\$4,235.67, up 2.3% on the day.\" |\n| Replying above / Answer below | \"OK so basically the issue is that the dedupe only fires for texts of length >= 10...\" |\n| Compound: OK, that's the fix. / 已发, 不再追加. / Sent above #22141. | Long acks that wrap into real content |\n| Case + emoji stripping: OK 👍 / '  sent  ' | Empty / whitespace-only text |\n| Media payloads with meta-ack captions | (media always preserved) |\n\n## Behavioural guarantees\n\n- **Zero impact on agents that don't use the message tool.** `sentTexts.length === 0` short-circuits the filter.\n- **Zero impact on media payloads.** Caption text is checked but media is always preserved.\n- **No regressions on real replies.** Anchored patterns + 200-char cap + 20-char trailing-content limit make false positives extremely rare; the \"Real replies\" column in the test matrix covers the boundary cases.\n\n## Repro before / after\n\nBefore this patch:\n- User asks question\n- Agent calls `message(action=send, content=\"Here is the analysis...\")`\n- Channel shows message #1: \"Here is the analysis...\"\n- Agent's final reply: \"已发 #22141, 不再追加\"\n- Channel shows message #2 (duplicate): \"已发 #22141, 不再追加\"\n\nAfter this patch:\n- Same flow\n- Channel shows message #1: \"Here is the analysis...\"\n- \"已发 #22141, 不再追加\" is suppressed by `filterMessagingToolMetaCommentary` (matched the Chinese ack pattern + 8-char trailing comment, within 20-char limit)\n- Channel only shows message #1",
        "branch": "fix/suppress-post-tool-send-meta-commentary",
